programme.desc: Television presenter and avid "Most Haunted" viewer Gaby Roslin joins the team in Cheshire. As events escalate, a curious combination of baths, bees and books ensures a far from pleasant stay.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Black Swan Hotel, Devizes, Wiltshire
programme.desc: The team investigates the scene of a centuries-old crime, but can they identify both victim and villain? Guest psychic Uri Geller helps to unearth a deep, dark and shocking secret.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Kinnitty Castle, County Offaly, Republic of Ireland
programme.desc: A warm welcome awaits the team across the Irish Sea. But, as night falls and the lights go out, a series of startling and eerie events shake the member of the crew to their cores.
programme.sub-title: Kinnitty Castle, County Offaly, Republic of Ireland

programme.title: Most Haunted: Castle Leslie, County Monaghan, Republic of Ireland
programme.desc: Who haunts Castle Leslie and why won't they leave? As they attempt to make contact, the team is shocked and amazed at the response that they receive from beyond the grave.
programme.sub-title: Castle Leslie, County Monaghan, Republic of Ireland

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Brightest Star
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark meet a child star whose fame is spoiling her rotten, destroying her family and taking away her childhood.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Investment In Caring
programme.desc: Jonathan encourages residents in a neighborhood to unite against a cold-hearted developer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Right Thing
programme.desc: Jonathan inspires a young man to help the grandfather who has recently been placed in a nursing home.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 1
programme.desc: Lizzy MacGill is a horse trainer's young daughter who elopes with Garth Armstrong, a privileged man.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark try to help Lizzie. The new bride has cancer and she is pregnant.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 1
programme.desc: Mark and Jonathan become counselors at a camp for children with cancer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are helping patients at Camp Good Times in different ways. But a father still refuses to deal with his son's illness.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand
programme.desc: Everyone wants to look younger but if you work hard and play hard like Sue Whyte, it's far tougher to roll back those years. Sue's already stopped smoking and lost a lot of weight so can Fiona McDonald and her team of time warriors take care of the rest?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Pain No Gain
programme.desc: Once a sun-worshipping fashion model, Linda led a charmed life of good looks. After the devastating loss of her family, life became difficult. Linda is willing to do anything to recover her former looks and finds out that beauty comes with a price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back
programme.desc: In her youth, Catherine was a wild child punk rocker whose bright red mohawk got her elected homecoming queen. But now that Catherine is a single mother of twin teenage daughters, she feels like she's lost her young, eye-catching style.
programme.sub-title: The Homecoming Queen Gets Her Crown Back

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Guilty Of Needing A Makeover
programme.desc: After a career as a cop and a private investigator, Lita worked her way through law school while raising her son. She's finished school and taken the bar exam, but her face and body have paid the price.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Prepping For The Big Day
programme.desc: Lilia is the first in her family to finish college. She helps support her family and bought a house she shares with her mother. Her achievements have carried a price; she looks old and tired compared to her friends.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A New Look On Life
programme.desc: At one time Trisha was a golden locked, free-spirited surfer, but once she settled down and had children her looks and self-esteem took a downward spiral. Suddenly single again, Trisha needs help searching for her energetic youth.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Out of Hiding
programme.desc: Tammy has lost over 100 pounds, but says she feels like she actually looks older! After years of hiding under oversized clothes and bulky glasses, she doesn't know how to dress and take care of her new body.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Debbie Rotchell
programme.desc: Essex girl Debbie Rotchell, 49, smokes 15,000 cigarettes a year and loves to sunbathe. Debbie gets a wake-up call when a poll of one hundred people puts her at 55. Just as well Nicky Hambleton-Jones is on hand with her time-fighting trio.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Military Makeover
programme.desc: As former Marine, Kimberly wasn't "trained" in the art of looking feminine and as a single mother of three, now isn't the time for her to begin learning. She just doesn't have the time. Time to make Kimberly look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hairy Mary Quite Contrary
programme.desc: Mary is an overworked telecommuter and mother of twin 5-year-old girls. Since she works from home, Mary has traded in her business suits for sweats and a ponytail. We'll see if we can make Mary look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Better Days Ahead
programme.desc: Serena came to the U.S. from Cambodia at age seven and helped care for her younger siblings. She loves them, but does not love being mistaken for their mother. Serena had to grow up too fast, but she doesn't have to look like it.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Rosy Red To Peaches And Cream
programme.desc: Monica is a working mother of three whose rosacea has gotten worse with every passing year and she is tired of hearing, 'Oh, you've been out in the sun?' The team injects motivation back into Monica's life and look.
programme.sub-title: From Rosy Red To Peaches And Cream

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Faith in a New Look
programme.desc: Peggy is a single chaplain who uses her faith and people skills helping sick children in a children's hospital. She wants to regain her confidence with a younger, sassier look – that's where we come in. It's time to make Peggy look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Backstage To Center Stage
programme.desc: Mimi was a successful touring backup singer, and decided to take a final bow after getting married and having her daughter. Now that her daughter is older, she is ready to jump back on stage and needs the look to match.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Bummed Out To Belle Of The Ball
programme.desc: Jennifer has been feeling older since her back injury six months ago. Her job requires shopping in Beverly Hills and attending charity balls in appropriate attire. But at six feet tall, size 16 and on a budget, this is no easy task. She needs a makeover!

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Abduction
programme.desc: A volunteer who was working to interpret an ancient message from Ma'el assaults Da'an and escapes through a portal. Sandoval helps Da'an avoid interrogation from Zo'or while they try to locate her.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Arrival
programme.desc: A Taelon shuttle is shot down over Antarctica. There are Jiridians aboard, but two of the passengers escape. When Augur discovers Lili's blood on the ship, he is convinced that she is not dead.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Forge of Creation
programme.desc: Lili, Vorjak, and the baby flee to find a shuttle to escape Earth. Liam and Sandoval are both tracking them - for different reasons. Augur is on the run from volunteers, but sends a friend (Juliet) to help Liam while he's gone.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: First Breath
programme.desc: A college friend of Renee's resurfaces and leads them on an investigation of the link between the Taelons and a biomedical facility's cloning operation.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Sins of the Father
programme.desc: A Senator's daughter is found to have kryss in her system. Liam and Renee suspect the Taelons lied about synthesizing it and there is a new location for production. They believe Federov is involved. Da'an is addicted to kryss.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Limbo
programme.desc: The Taelons lend some of their dwindling core energy to Joshua Doors for a pilot cold fusion project, but the energy is stolen, leaving the Taelons vulnerable. Jonathan Doors lives on as an AI in cyberspace.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Motherlode
programme.desc: Augur is caught and placed in a special prison where he is placed in a sensory deprivation chamber. An amoralist gets him out and wants Augur to help him steal the gold Zo'or has on the mothership. When Liam learns of what happened he tries to find Augur.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Take No Prisoners
programme.desc: The ANA negotiate amnesty for all resistance members, Liam tries to convince resistance member Halley Simmons to take the offer. Sandoval uses parasites to make volunteers do suicide missions against the resistance.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Second Wave
programme.desc: The Taelons decide to leave Earth when it appears that the Jiridians are invading. Meanwhile, a group of Resistance prisoners saved from the mother ship include several disguised Jiridians who are causing trouble for Liam and Renee.
